# Speech-to-Text Application Structure

This Deepgram-powered Speech-to-Text application uses a modular architecture:

## Entry Points
- [main.py](mdc:main.py): The primary entry point that initializes the GUI and transcription agent
- [STT-dg.py](mdc:STT-dg.py): Alternative standalone version with all functionality in one file
- [build_exe.py](mdc:build_exe.py): Builds a single-file executable with PyInstaller

## Core Components
- [config.py](mdc:config.py): Central configuration including UI settings, hotkeys, and Deepgram parameters
- [transcription/agent.py](mdc:transcription/agent.py): Main transcription controller that coordinates audio capture and processing
- [ui/gui.py](mdc:ui/gui.py): The GUI implementation using CustomTkinter

## Utilities
- [utils/icon_converter.py](mdc:utils/icon_converter.py): Utility for converting PNG to ICO format for application icons
